definitions.definition: The regions in which a sheriff has authority.
examples: Crossing the river got him beyond his old nemesis' sheriffdom and into the territory of a more liberal authority.

definitions.definition: The office, or period of office, of a sheriff.
examples: His sheriffdom began with his election and ended with his death.

main_definition: The regions in which a sheriff has authority.
secondary_definitions: The office, or period of office, of a sheriff.
